<br>
One of the big pains of being a cleric is the poor travelling abilities. This annoys me more than not being able to solo much. One big benefit of Halflings is they have a racial Sneak/Hide ability. While this is not the same as true Invisibility it is the best a cleric can hope for. It can make it easier to get to and from where you will get groups.<br>
<br>
I still like your gnome idea but - especially on FV - be sure you know why you are playing that character. &quot;I made a dwarf cleric because it has the best stats&quot; is not an explanation that flies here. &quot;..because they get the best beer&quot; would be far better.<br>
<br>
Almost all gnomes I have met have been lecherous. I suppose it is their vantage point that does it. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukristinbluecanary.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kristin Blue Canary</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/30/02 9:49:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2738.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting a grouping class...too late?</span><hr size=1> If you're caught between Gnome and Halfling Cleric, then look from an RP perspective...<br>
<br>
Halflings are Clerics of Bristlebane.  Trickster priests are a *very* cool concept - it's like you get to play Coyote of Native American legend, teaching lessons (sometimes really hard ones!) through your sense of humor.  There's always, of course, the famous Tickle-Rez technique of Niami DenMother, the High Muckety Momma of EQ Traders - the character Niami performs Rezzes IC by tickling the feet of the deceased.  *grins*  (I can't help it...I love the DenMother and EQTraders.  *chuckle*)<br>
<br>
Gnomes are Clerics of Brell or Bertoxxulous.  It's harder for me to characterize the former, because some Brell-worshippers really like other Brell-folk (Dwarves) and others don't (the old, &quot;we're Brell's REAL children&quot; thing).  I have noticed some lecherous Gnomes, but I think that actually goes along with Brell's earthy warrior nature in some ways.  They might be more intellectual than Dwarves, but they still live underground, and if they still worship Brell, they will have an appreciation for the simple things in life as well as their cogs and machines.<br>
<br>
Bertox Clerics, well, the &quot;Be healed, Shadowknight, to spread the death and decay of our Master&quot; line usually helps with any conflict you might have between being a devotee of entropy and death and still flinging heals, and it's a damn interesting perspective to have on a Cleric's job.  Evil Gnomes are fun.  The Dread Gnome Pirates and many of the Evil Gnomes I've met on FV are way cool *salute* and being pint sized and very, very evil is, just, well, amusing.  (I have a Gnome Gnecro on my home server, and that is just a blast.)<br>
<br>
Whichever you choose, give the character a bit of history and motivation, and RP whenever you can.  It makes this server great.<br>
<br>
BC.<br>
She of many, many incarnations.<br>
Currently Kiriki, Gnome Wizard of Brell <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ua11e.showPublicProfile?language=EN>A11e</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/30/02 11:41:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2738.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Consider a soloing class</span><hr size=1> You are right to consider the server population in deciding your class.  Unless you have a preset group of friends or make friends quickly, you might want to reconsider being a cleric.  Clerics have a tough time finding a group on FV at times.  Your choice of locations to hunt will be very limited as you will have to stick to higher population zones.<br>
<br>
You might want to consider a soloing class instead.  With all the attention Verant has showered on druids lately - especially the new high end 75% Complete Heal, I would pick a druid over a cleric if I wanted to start a priest class.  Druids solo well virtually their entire game playing life.  Throw in ports and, well, you get the picture.  Two druids in a group stack well - one heals and buffs, the other nukes, thorns and DOTs.  2 clerics don't stack well.  Clerics can't melee well and have mediocre nukes.<br>
<br>
The new cleric melee skills won't kick in till the high 50s (except bash).  The fact that druids can heal almost as well as clerics and get a big boost at 58 will probably cut into the ability of clerics to get high end experience groups (clerics still needed for raids but you can't get decent exp from raiding).  Cleric abilities don't match up well against druid abilities.<br>
<br>
Verant is clueless right now about what to do to fix clerics without turning them into paladins.  Look for an extended period of experimentation before/if they ever get clerics fixed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gravesfv>Graves FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/28/02 6:51:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2738.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Consider a soloing class</span><hr size=1> I had a Bristlebane Gnome Cleric up to 43 on my old server years ago.  Gnomes can follow Bertox (I chose him here ~ Bertox Newb Cleric), Brell, Bristlebane (clerics and rogues), Solusek Ro (wizard) and Rallos Zek (warriors) in addition to agnostic.<br>
